        <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;" id="pop_facts">
            Berea Population Facts
        </h3>
    


            <h4>What is the current population of Berea?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Berea is 15,924.  Berea, Kentucky is the 2,263rd largest city in the US.
            </p>

            
                <h4>What county is Berea, Kentucky in?</h4>
                <p>
                
                    Berea is located entirely in 
                    Madison County.
                
                </p>
            

            
                
                    <h4>What is the size of Berea, Kentucky in square miles?</h4>
                    Berea has an area of 
                    16.0 square miles.

                    
                    
                
            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Berea?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The current population of Berea (15,924) is it's peak population.
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Berea growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Berea has grown
                        40.5% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Berea, Kentucky is growing somewhat quickly;
                        it is growing faster than 73%
                        of similarly sized cities since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            
                <h4>What is the population density of Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                Berea has a population density of
                846.9 people
                per square mile.

                
                
                </p>
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
