        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="demographics">
            Berea Demographics
        </h3>
    


            
                

                
                <h4>What is the voting age population of Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Berea, Kentucky, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 11,322.  The voting age population is 47.1% male and 52.9% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 13.2% of
                        the residents of Berea are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Berea are 91.2% White, 3.9% Black, 2.8% Two or more races, 1.1% Other, 0.6% Asian and 0.5% American Indian. Additionally, 4.9% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Berea, 19.8% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 21.0%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    16.5% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Berea.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 59.9% of
                    Berea residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Berea, Kentucky residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    86.2% of
                    Berea residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 29.4%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 11.3%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Berea residents aged 5 and older, 6.3% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                4.0% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                1.5% speak an Indo-European language, and
                0.6% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="labor">
            Berea Income &amp; Labor Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Berea is 4.9%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Berea, 15.1% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Berea is $44,292.</p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="housing">
            Berea Housing &amp; Rent Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Berea, 51.7% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
                </p>
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are rented in Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    Renters occupy 48.3% of housing units in
                    Berea.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky housing units were built before 1940?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Of all the housing units in Berea,
                        5.2% of them were build before 1940.
                    </p>
                

                
                

                
                    <h4>What percentage of Berea, Kentucky housing units were built after 2000?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Berea, 26.4% of the 
                    total housing units were built
                    
                        after the year 2000, which is approximately 
                        
                            1,600 units.
                        
                    
                    </p>
                
                
                
                
                <h4>What is the median monthly rent in Berea, Kentucky?</h4>
                <p>
                    The median gross monthly rent payment for renters in Berea is
                    $715.
                </p>

                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of households in Berea, Kentucky have broadband internet?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Berea, 79.8% of households have
                    an active broadband internet connection.
                </p>
                
                
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
